1 (2) A person who violates subsection (a) of this section with the intent to
2 use the firearm or dangerous weapon to commit a crime shall be imprisoned
3 for not more than five years or fined not more than $10,000.00, or both.
4 (c) This section shall not apply to:
5 (1) a firearm or dangerous weapon carried for legitimate law
6 enforcement purposes by a federal law enforcement officer or a law
7 enforcement officer certified as a law enforcement officer by the Vermont
8 Criminal Justice Council pursuant to 20 V.S.A. § 2358;
9 (2) a firearm or dangerous weapon carried by a person while preforming
10 the person’s official duties as an employee of the United States; a department
11 or agency of the United States; a state; or a department, agency, or political
12 subdivision of a state if the person is authorized to carry a firearm or dangerous
13 weapon as part of the person’s official duties;
14 (3) a firearm or dangerous weapon carried by a member of the Vermont
15 National Guard, of the National Guard of another state, or of the U.S. Armed
16 Forces who is on duty and acting under state or federal orders;
17 (4) buildings or portions of buildings that are:
18 (A) owned or leased by the Department of Buildings and General
19 Services; and
20 (B) leased or subleased by the Department of Buildings and General
21 Services to private tenants for their exclusive use;
