12 (d) As used in this section:
13 (1) “Dangerous or deadly weapon” means a weapon, device, instrument,
14 material, or substance, whether animate or inanimate, that is used or readily
15 capable of being used to cause death or serious bodily injury, including an
16 explosive as defined in section 1603 of this title, except that “dangerous or
17 deadly weapon” does not include a pocket knife with a blade of less than 2.5
18 inches in length.
19 (2) “Firearm” has the same meaning as in subsection 4017(d) of this
20 title.
